Whisk together flour and oil in heavy 6-quart sauce pot over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes or until smooth and lightly browned. Stir in Cajun seasoning; cook 1 minute. Add tomatoes with juice, thyme and garlic; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes. Add salad; cook stirring 1 to 2 minutes. Add shrimp; cook, stirring, until heated through. Season with pepper, to taste.